Departed from the shores of Spain in search of another world, an intrepid flotilla sailed on far away seas which are present at the setting of the Sun. Uncertain off their way, they proceeded in a haphazard way on unknown waves. About them crowded innumerable Nereids. Nymphs of those unexplored seas, they had all left their damp homes to come and look upon those winged vessels, which, their sails to the wind, appeared to them to ssy upon the deep.
